As much as I love going in the gym and throwing a shit ton of weight around, it’s important to focus on performing the entire movement with the muscle you are trying to target. Example: If you are doing a lat pull down and you only feel it in your biceps, either your form is wrong, or you may just be going way to heavy. It’s essential for beginners to develop a mind to muscle connection to be able to perform the exercises while engaging the muscle being targeted.
